2. A More Robust Hall-Effect Layout
Instead of relying on a single sensor at the starting corner to track everything relatively, you can use Hall-effect sensors to give you absolute, row-by-row confirmation. Since Hall-effect sensors and small neodymium magnets are incredibly cheap in bulk, you can use them to establish precise indexing marks along the travel axes:

