1. Polarity and Grid Consistency
To make sure every house, wall, or tree can be rotated or placed anywhere on the board without being dynamically repelled, you must establish a strict polarity rule during assembly:

The Board: Every single column cap must have its magnet facing the exact same direction (e.g., North pole facing up).

