The "Hidden" Magnet Trick: You can program your 3D printer to pause right before it closes the top layers of the cap. You drop the magnet into the printed pocket, and the printer finishes printing right over it. This completely hides the magnet inside the plastic, keeping the column top perfectly flat and smooth while maintaining the magnetic pull.

3. Designing the "Snapping" Terrain Feature
Because the terrain features (like a 3×3 inch house) will span multiple columns, you don't actually need a magnet for every single square inch of the building's footprint.

